# Code Language Convention

All code and technical identifiers must be written in **English**. The only exception is **user-facing text** (visible to end users), which may be in Spanish or the target language of the project.

## Must Be in English

- **Component names**: `ContactSection`, `HeroSection`, `CtaBanner` (not `SeccionContacto`)
- **File names**: `contact-section.astro`, `hero-section.astro`
- **Variable and function names**: `handleSubmit`, `isLoading`, `userData`
- **CSS class names**: `cta-button`, `section-heading`
- **Comments and documentation**: `// Validate form before submit`
- **Attribute names, IDs, data attributes**: `data-testid="submit-btn"`

## Exception: User-Facing Text

- Button labels, headings, paragraphs, alt text, meta descriptions
- Example: `<h1>Agenda tu hora</h1>`, `alt="Clínica dental"`

## Examples

```astro
<!-- ✅ GOOD -->
<button class="cta-button">Agenda tu hora</button>
<section id="contact-section">...</section>

<!-- ❌ BAD -->
<button class="boton-cta">Agenda tu hora</button>
<section id="seccion-contacto">...</section>
```
